Somebody, help!

35
00:07:58,940 --> 00:08:02,050
- Call an ambulance!
- Thee!

36
00:08:02,050 --> 00:08:04,200
Hurry up!

37
00:08:14,910 --> 00:08:15,910
Thee!

38
00:08:16,870 --> 00:08:18,020
Thee!

39
00:08:18,590 --> 00:08:19,590
Thee...

40
00:08:21,430 --> 00:08:23,500
- Doctor, could you...
- Yes...

41
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:29,750
What are you going to do?

42
00:08:31,536 --> 00:08:33,140
Would you like me to help?

43
00:08:36,603 --> 00:08:39,593
No, I don't. Don't bother!

44
00:08:41,030 --> 00:08:44,380
He's lost too much blood, he won't last long.

45
00:08:49,190 --> 00:08:52,060
Get blood that's the same type as this guard's.

46
00:09:33,670 --> 00:09:36,140
- Please, wait outside.
- Thee!

47
00:09:36,140 --> 00:09:38,980
- Please, wait outside.
- Please help my friend. Thee!

48
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:57,260
Doctor, do you remember?

49
00:09:57,260 --> 00:10:01,700
My friend was the one
who helped you at the basketball court.

50
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,000
Hey!

51
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:18,600
Hey!

52
00:10:38,196 --> 00:10:39,626
Who started it?

53
00:10:42,096 --> 00:10:43,180
Him.

54
00:10:44,430 --> 00:10:45,710
Hey.

55
00:10:45,710 --> 00:10:47,660
Hey, you punched Kom first.

56
00:10:48,910 --> 00:10:49,910
Stop!

57
00:11:11,030 --> 00:11:13,740
It was my fault, sir.

58
00:11:14,670 --> 00:11:16,860
Please, only punish me.

59
00:11:18,030 --> 00:11:20,130
Don't tell his parents.

60
00:11:20,130 --> 00:11:22,220
This got messy because of me.

61
00:11:40,990 --> 00:11:45,080
You've hurt many of his guys.
He won't back down that easily.

62
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:47,150
He thinks his dad's a big shot, I guess.

63
00:11:47,150 --> 00:11:49,060
That's why he acts all tough.

64
00:11:51,870 --> 00:11:54,700
His dad's definitely going to come after us.

65
00:12:03,950 --> 00:12:07,020
Thee!

66
00:12:36,003 --> 00:12:38,590
[Please contact the Forensic Unit
to claim the body]

67
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:44,700
Suthee, dear.

68
00:12:45,990 --> 00:12:48,140
It's mom.

69
00:13:00,623 --> 00:13:02,880
Why did you go berserk like that?

70
00:13:02,880 --> 00:13:04,300
I was actually scared.

71
00:13:08,310 --> 00:13:09,460
What are you looking at?

72
00:13:13,990 --> 00:13:15,060
I don't know.

73
00:13:16,050 --> 00:13:17,180
I just did it.

74
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:23,570
Yes. But I'm sorry

75
00:13:23,570 --> 00:13:26,300
for saying that I helped those two.

76
00:13:27,150 --> 00:13:30,030
Seeing you help them so selflessly

77
00:13:30,030 --> 00:13:32,300
made me want to be like you.

78
00:13:35,043 --> 00:13:36,620
Suthee.

79
00:13:42,510 --> 00:13:45,300
Why is this happening?

80
00:13:49,110 --> 00:13:50,540
Can I interview you, please?
[Strictly Prohibited Area]

81
00:13:50,540 --> 00:13:52,900
How did the killer get into the prison?

82
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:54,580
We're still investigating.

83
00:13:54,580 --> 00:13:56,300
Is the killer really a psychopath?

84
00:13:56,300 --> 00:13:57,980
Of course, definitely a psychopath.

85
00:14:01,270 --> 00:14:04,070
- How did you find that out?
- Is this the same one from the news?

86
00:14:04,070 --> 00:14:06,080
- Is the killer really a psychopath?
- Really?

87
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:08,020
- So, is that right?
- Is he really a psychopath?

88
00:14:08,020 --> 00:14:12,310
- When did you find out?
- When did you really find out?

89
00:14:12,310 --> 00:14:14,180
Could you please answer?

90
00:14:15,790 --> 00:14:17,300
What do we do now, Captain?

91
00:14:18,350 --> 00:14:20,030
Let him sort it out with the Chief himself.

92
00:14:20,030 --> 00:14:21,340
Is this true?

93
00:14:22,230 --> 00:14:24,740
Whether this killer is a psychopath or not,

94
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:27,340
stay tuned to News Watch.

95
00:14:27,340 --> 00:14:29,330
This is Sujitra, reporting for M news.

96
00:14:29,330 --> 00:14:31,250
- He's here.
- Let's go, he's here.

97
00:14:31,250 --> 00:14:33,110
- Sir, can you please answer?
- Sir.

98
00:14:33,110 --> 00:14:36,660
Sir, with a serial killer on the loose like this,
how can the public feel safe?

99
00:14:36,660 --> 00:14:40,000
- Could you please answer, sir?
- How can the public feel safe?

100
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:43,310
- Could you please answer, sir?
- Yes, could you please answer?

101
00:14:43,310 --> 00:14:44,590
Please stay calm.

102
00:14:44,590 --> 00:14:47,260
Let me discuss with the minister first.

103
00:14:47,260 --> 00:14:50,100
If there's any update, I will inform you.

104
00:14:50,990 --> 00:14:52,020
Is that ok?

105
00:14:53,030 --> 00:14:55,260
But how long does it take?

106
00:14:55,260 --> 00:14:56,540
We're concerned about the safety of the public.

107
00:14:56,540 --> 00:14:58,550
The public is understandably fearful, sir.

108
00:14:58,550 --> 00:15:01,760
Please stay calm first. I have to go.

109
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:02,760
Sir!

110
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:06,000
Right now,
the public is completely fearful, sir.

111
00:15:06,836 --> 00:15:08,220
Follow the murder news...

112
00:15:08,220 --> 00:15:13,190
Picha, when you take some milk,
can you make a note of it?

113
00:15:13,190 --> 00:15:15,340
Look, the milk's all gone.

114
00:15:15,340 --> 00:15:16,660
What milk, Grandma?

115
00:15:16,660 --> 00:15:19,060
You know I don't drink milk.

116
00:15:19,608 --> 00:15:21,740
Wait, where did it disappear to?

117
00:15:22,721 --> 00:15:26,220
How did it disappear?

118
00:15:31,230 --> 00:15:32,660
- Auntie.
- Yes.

119
00:15:32,660 --> 00:15:34,140
Can we get three bottles of milk?

120
00:15:34,140 --> 00:15:36,340
Yes. Get them yourself.

121
00:15:49,430 --> 00:15:52,100
Don't forget to close the fridge door tightly.

122
00:15:58,656 --> 00:15:59,910
You guys again.

123
00:15:59,910 --> 00:16:03,230
Grandma, take some rest. Your leg still hurts.

124
00:16:03,230 --> 00:16:04,700
You don't have to keep working, you know.

125
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:08,140
Well, it doesn't hurt that much.

126
00:16:08,140 --> 00:16:12,460
Today, you'd better come home early.
Don't be later than 6 p.m.

127
00:16:12,990 --> 00:16:16,830
How can I get back that early?
The shop closes at 9 p.m.

128
00:16:16,830 --> 00:16:19,060
Can you not work for a while?

129
00:16:19,060 --> 00:16:21,780
Check out the news. I'm worried about you.

130
00:16:21,780 --> 00:16:23,580
How can I do that, Grandma?

131
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:28,260
Okay, I'll come pick you up then.

132
00:16:34,367 --> 00:16:35,380
Can you do that?

133
00:16:36,147 --> 00:16:39,630
Alright, then I'll have someone else
pick you up.

134
00:16:39,630 --> 00:16:42,580
No, I'm good. I'll get back with Meena.

135
00:16:42,580 --> 00:16:45,790
- Don't you understand, I'm worried about you.
- I'm going now.

136
00:16:45,790 --> 00:16:47,940
Why are you so stubborn?

137
00:16:57,238 --> 00:16:58,580
What took you so long, Captain?

138
00:16:58,580 --> 00:16:59,890
He's waiting for you.

139
00:16:59,890 --> 00:17:01,690
Who the hell's waiting for me?
The Prime Minister's son?

140
00:17:01,690 --> 00:17:03,420
- The Prime Minister.
- Huh?

141
00:17:08,181 --> 00:17:09,181
You're serious? The PM's here?

142
00:17:09,801 --> 00:17:13,000
I've received the full incident report,

143
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:16,960
and the reporter described the suspect
as a "Psychopath."

144
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:19,500
Now, people are just terrified.

145
00:17:20,671 --> 00:17:23,230
The only way to stop this news

146
00:17:23,230 --> 00:17:25,900
is to find the killer urgently.

147
00:17:30,584 --> 00:17:32,620
Have you found any clues yet?

148
00:17:33,487 --> 00:17:36,770
There have been three cases so far,
and the killer has not been arrested yet.

149
00:17:36,770 --> 00:17:37,790
Uh...

150
00:17:39,248 --> 00:17:40,710
Well,

151
00:17:40,710 --> 00:17:45,140
the special investigation unit
has been on-site for every case.

152
00:17:45,140 --> 00:17:49,806
We've also been keeping track of various leads.

153
00:17:49,806 --> 00:17:50,806
Uh...

154
00:17:56,514 --> 00:18:02,940
For the progress, I have assigned Captain Ramil
to oversee this case directly.

155
00:18:02,940 --> 00:18:04,700
He will provide all reports on the matter.

156
00:18:11,694 --> 00:18:14,740
So it was you who brought up
this psychopath story.

157
00:18:15,539 --> 00:18:17,940
Everyone is terrified.

158
00:18:18,658 --> 00:18:20,700
How will you take responsibility
for this matter?

159
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:42,980
[Maga One City Police Station]

160
00:18:46,101 --> 00:18:49,030
From now on, let Angkan handle
all updates with the press.

161
00:18:49,030 --> 00:18:51,790
As for you, you should start thinking
before you speak.

162
00:18:51,790 --> 00:18:54,420
Better yet, just don't speak at all.

163
00:18:58,313 --> 00:18:59,313
Hey!

164
00:19:00,826 --> 00:19:02,556
Hey. Hey!

165
00:19:14,784 --> 00:19:15,670
Captain.

166
00:19:15,670 --> 00:19:17,100
I'm Sergeant First Class Patcharawit

167
00:19:17,100 --> 00:19:18,840
from Development Area 1 station.

168
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:19,840
And?

169
00:19:20,586 --> 00:19:22,980
I want to be on your team, Captain.

170
00:19:24,890 --> 00:19:26,070
What are you responsible for?

171
00:19:26,070 --> 00:19:27,310
I'm on patrol.

172
00:19:27,310 --> 00:19:29,860
I want to join your team
and help catch the killer.

173
00:19:31,139 --> 00:19:32,139
No.

174
00:19:33,982 --> 00:19:35,300
Why, Captain?

175
00:19:36,491 --> 00:19:38,100
You have no experience.

176
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:40,860
The killer's a psychopath.
You're going to risk your life for nothing.

177
00:19:40,860 --> 00:19:42,500
But I have to catch him.

178
00:19:44,695 --> 00:19:46,180
He killed my friend, Captain.

179
00:19:49,470 --> 00:19:51,140
I'm ready to risk my life.

180
00:20:06,416 --> 00:20:09,150
I'm sorry, but I really can't
provide that information.

181
00:20:09,150 --> 00:20:10,540
Uh, okay then.

182
00:20:18,796 --> 00:20:19,830
Hello.

183
00:20:19,830 --> 00:20:23,020
I'm Chanya from M News,
a reporter for the News Deep Dive program.

184
00:20:23,020 --> 00:20:24,740
I interviewed you last time.

185
00:20:24,740 --> 00:20:26,100
Do you remember?

186
00:20:27,293 --> 00:20:29,820
Would it be possible if I could...

187
00:20:29,820 --> 00:20:32,470
Hello, reporter. We're not doing interviews
at the moment.

188
00:20:32,470 --> 00:20:35,820
Oh, okay. Thank you.

189
00:20:57,887 --> 00:20:59,550
Hey, what's up?

190
00:20:59,550 --> 00:21:00,830
Lieutenant Chin.

191
00:21:00,830 --> 00:21:03,700
Where's Captain Ramil working on a case today?

192
00:21:04,998 --> 00:21:06,580
I can't tell you.

193
00:21:06,580 --> 00:21:09,790
If the Captain knows you called,

194
00:21:09,790 --> 00:21:11,500
he'll be mad at me for sure.

195
00:21:13,193 --> 00:21:16,620
What if I ask you off the record? Is that okay?

196
00:21:17,783 --> 00:21:19,830
Off the record... Oh, yes.

197
00:21:21,463 --> 00:21:23,493
Where's he going today?

198
00:22:26,950 --> 00:22:29,180
Do you have any updates, Captain?

199
00:22:29,990 --> 00:22:33,260
You don't really keep me updated these days.

200
00:22:34,750 --> 00:22:36,220
So, what did you find out?

201
00:22:37,590 --> 00:22:38,980
Why did the Prime Minister come?

202
00:22:44,235 --> 00:22:46,380
He came to stop us from giving case information
to reporters.

203
00:22:50,704 --> 00:22:53,420
If I ask, will you tell me?

204
00:22:58,684 --> 00:23:00,140
Let's get to the point,

205
00:23:00,140 --> 00:23:01,980
what are you doing here today?

206
00:23:06,057 --> 00:23:08,317
Have you ever had any problems
with the prison guard?

207
00:23:08,870 --> 00:23:11,380
- No, I haven't.
- Were you with anyone, or alone?

208
00:23:11,380 --> 00:23:13,590
Where were you on the day of the incident?

209
00:23:13,590 --> 00:23:16,130
I was in my cell that time.

210
00:23:16,130 --> 00:23:18,000
I was just sitting around.

211
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:22,000
- Did you see anyone?
- No, I didn't.

212
00:23:27,630 --> 00:23:31,120
- Oh, I was in my cell that time.
- What were you doing?

213
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:32,300
Oh, I was in the bathroom.

214
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:36,230
- Did you see anyone?
- No.

215
00:23:37,990 --> 00:23:40,740
No one seemed suspicious on that day.
[Chanya]

216
00:23:49,390 --> 00:23:52,660
The guard was nice and kind.

217
00:23:52,660 --> 00:23:56,470
The last time I saw the guard was
when he came to set up the stage.

218
00:23:56,470 --> 00:23:58,540
Then, I went back to the cell block.

219
00:23:59,350 --> 00:24:01,510
Did anyone go backstage after that?

220
00:24:01,510 --> 00:24:03,330
- No, nobody did.
- No, sir.

221
00:24:03,330 --> 00:24:04,700
Everyone went back to the cell block.

222
00:24:11,110 --> 00:24:14,450
Has Suthee had any problems with anyone?

223
00:24:14,450 --> 00:24:18,690
I don't think he has, except...

224
00:24:18,690 --> 00:24:20,260
Did he have any arguments with anyone?

225
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:23,780
I've seen Suthee argue with Dr. Orachun, sir.

226
00:24:23,780 --> 00:24:24,780
Orachun?

227
00:24:25,701 --> 00:24:26,701
Yes, sir.

228
00:24:28,230 --> 00:24:29,230
Alright.

229
00:24:44,302 --> 00:24:47,030
How much do you know about this? Tell me.

230
00:24:47,030 --> 00:24:50,100
What's going on between your friend Suthee
and that bastard Orachun?

231
00:24:50,859 --> 00:24:51,859
Uh,

232
00:24:55,686 --> 00:24:59,540
from what I've heard directly from him...

233
00:25:41,387 --> 00:25:43,100
Why is your food better than theirs?

234
00:25:44,133 --> 00:25:45,620
What kind of privilege do you have?

235
00:25:55,587 --> 00:25:57,660
Do you really think this world's fair?

236
00:26:01,079 --> 00:26:03,350
Why? What are you missing

237
00:26:03,350 --> 00:26:05,980
that makes you want to be equal
with everyone else?

238
00:26:10,661 --> 00:26:11,860
Look at this creature,

239
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:16,900
do you think it's equal to other animals?

240
00:26:33,990 --> 00:26:35,310
Come on!

241
00:26:35,310 --> 00:26:37,260
One wrong move and I'll get you, you bastard.

242
00:26:45,030 --> 00:26:50,220
Suthee always wondered why Orachun
got more privileges than the other prisoners,

243
00:26:51,270 --> 00:26:55,670
and why Orachun had been doing fine
in prison all those 25 years.

244
00:26:55,670 --> 00:26:57,940
He's just a death row inmate.

245
00:27:03,694 --> 00:27:05,130
Besides Orachun,

246
00:27:05,130 --> 00:27:06,980
did Suthee have problems with anyone else?

247
00:27:08,272 --> 00:27:09,393
I don't think so, Captain.

248
00:27:09,393 --> 00:27:12,836
He was also a good fellow at the college.

249
00:27:12,836 --> 00:27:18,130
So your friend was brave.
And this gave Orachun the motive to kill him.

250
00:27:18,130 --> 00:27:19,220
Motivation to kill?

251
00:27:20,744 --> 00:27:22,390
What do you mean, Captain?

252
00:27:22,390 --> 00:27:25,830
Are you saying that Orachun killed my friend?

253
00:27:25,830 --> 00:27:27,180
What do you think?

254
00:27:28,369 --> 00:27:30,180
It's not possible, Captain.

255
00:27:30,180 --> 00:27:33,380
Orachun offered to help stop Suthee's bleeding.

256
00:27:33,380 --> 00:27:38,100
The most suspicious one will act neutral.

257
00:27:38,100 --> 00:27:39,640
Remember that.

258
00:27:39,640 --> 00:27:40,640
Uh.

259
00:27:52,666 --> 00:27:53,666
How's it going?

260
00:27:55,183 --> 00:27:57,710
The prisoner is ready
for the interrogation, Captain.

261
00:27:57,710 --> 00:27:58,710
This way, please.

262
00:28:02,750 --> 00:28:03,870
Where are you guys?

263
00:28:03,870 --> 00:28:06,980
Better hurry, I'll wait upstairs.

264
00:28:28,842 --> 00:28:29,842
Handcuffs?

